  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>This delicate robe is made from thousands of pages torn from books, intricately folded together without a single thread to bind them.</em></p><p><strong>1st Level:</strong> While you wear this armor, you gain a +6 bonus to Stamina. Additionally, you can use a main action to fold in on yourself until you and your gear are paper thin. This effect lasts for 1 minute, letting you easily slip through any opening that is 1 inch wide or more. When you return to your three-dimensional form, you are [[/apply dazed]] for 1 minute. If you return to your true form while in a space that is too small for you, you are violently expelled into the nearest open space of your choice and take [[/damage 3d6]] damage.</p><p><strong>5th Level:</strong> The armor’s bonus to Stamina increases to +12, and when you return to your true form, you are [[/apply dazed turn]] only until the end of your next turn. Additionally, while you are paper thin, you can use a maneuver to wrap yourself around an adjacent target who is the same size or smaller than you, automatically [[/apply grabbed]]{grabbing} them.</p><p><strong>9th Level:</strong> The armor’s bonus to Stamina increases to +21, and you are no longer dazed when you return to your true form. Additionally, while you have a target [[/aplly grabbed]] when you are paper thin, you can use a maneuver to constrict the target, dealing [[/damage 10]] damage to them. A creature damaged this way takes a bane when using the Escape Grab maneuver against you and when making strikes against you.</p>",
